# Homelab Context

This is a GitOps-driven homelab running on a Mac mini M4 with OrbStack Kubernetes, managed by ArgoCD.

## Architecture

```mermaid
flowchart TD
  subgraph L0["Layer 0 ‚Äî Terraform (run once)"]
    TF[terraform apply] --> ArgoCDHelm[ArgoCD Helm Release]
    TF --> BootSecrets[Bootstrap Secrets]
    TF --> InfisicalApp[Infisical App CR]
  end
  subgraph L1["Layer 1 ‚Äî ArgoCD (every push to main)"]
    AppOfApps[App of Apps] -->|syncs| Services["k8s/apps/* manifests"]
  end
  subgraph L2["Layer 2 ‚Äî Secrets (never in git)"]
    Infisical[Infisical] --> ESO[External Secrets Operator]
    ESO --> K8sSecrets[K8s Secrets]
  end
  ArgoCDHelm --> AppOfApps
  GitPush["git push main"] --> L1
  K8sSecrets -->|consumed by| Services
```

## Core Rules

- All persistent cluster changes go through git ‚Üí ArgoCD sync. Never use `kubectl apply` for long-lived resources.
- Never commit secrets, API keys, or credentials to git. Use the Infisical ‚Üí ESO pipeline (`/secret-management` skill).
- ArgoCD Application CRs must follow the project and label conventions in `k8s/apps/argocd/README.md` (projects: `secrets`, `data`, `apps`; labels: `app.kubernetes.io/{name,part-of,component,managed-by}`).
- Prefer Kustomize over Helm for app workloads. Helm is only used for upstream charts (ESO, Infisical).
- Before modifying Helm `valuesObject`, always verify keys with `helm show values` ‚Äî charts silently ignore unknown keys. See `kubernetes.mdc` for the full rule.
- After merging changes to `main`, verify ArgoCD sync and pod health before considering the task complete. If services degrade, use the `/incident-response` skill.
- Documentation lives in `docs/` and is served by MkDocs. Use the `/documentation` skill for the update matrix and conventions.

## Git Workflow

The `main` branch is **protected**. Never push directly to `main` ‚Äî all changes require a feature branch and a pull request. Use the `/git-workflow` skill for the full branch workflow, PR creation, and post-merge cleanup procedures. Use `/address-issue` to execute the full issue-to-PR workflow.

## Key Paths

- `terraform/` ‚Äî Layer 0 bootstrap (ArgoCD, credentials)
- `k8s/apps/` ‚Äî Layer 1 GitOps manifests (one directory per service)
- `k8s/apps/argocd/` ‚Äî App of Apps: AppProjects + Application CRs
- `skills/` ‚Äî OpenClaw skills (mounted into pod at `/skills`)
- `agents/workspaces/` ‚Äî OpenClaw agent AGENTS.md personalities
- `.cursor/skills/` ‚Äî Cursor-local skills (git-workflow, documentation, release-management, secret-management, incident-response)
- `.cursor/agents/` ‚Äî Cursor subagents (verifier)
- `.cursor/commands/` ‚Äî Cursor commands (address-issue, pre-merge-check)
- `docs/` ‚Äî MkDocs documentation site

